      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Read all safety instructions before operating your Foredom power tool.</strong> They are for your protection and should always be followed to reduce the risk of personal injury or damage to the tool.
      </div>

      <h3>Required Personal Protective Equipment</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Safety glasses or face shield &mdash; always wear eye and face protection</li>
        <li>Respirator or dust mask &mdash; to prevent inhalation of dust particles or debris</li>
        <li>Heavy canvas or leather apron &mdash; recommended for carving and similar applications</li>
        <li>Closed-toe shoes &mdash; never wear open shoes or sandals</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>General Safety Rules</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Secure the workpiece in a vise or work-holding device. Holding it by hand can result in serious injury.</li>
        <li>Do not wear loose clothing or jewelry. Tie back long hair.</li>
        <li>Use a proper dust collection system to minimize accumulation of flammable or explosive dust.</li>
        <li>Secure the motor to its hanger or work surface. Flex shaft tools can jump at start-up or vibrate during operation.</li>
        <li>Never use an accessory at speeds above its maximum speed rating.</li>
        <li>Never use or continue to use any accessory that appears damaged, loose, vibrating, or out of balance.</li>
        <li>Always insert the shank of an accessory as far as possible into the collet or chuck and tighten securely.</li>
        <li>Never use excessive side pressure &mdash; let the speed of the accessory do the work.</li>
        <li>Do not stall the motor by jamming or using excessive pressure. This can damage the motor or flexible shaft.</li>
        <li>Never operate the motor with the outer sheath removed from the flexible shaft.</li>
        <li>Always disconnect the power cord before servicing the motor or removing the shaft or sheath.</li>
        <li>Never operate during a noticeable power decrease. Turn off and wait until full power is restored.</li>
        <li>Never use in an area where flammable vapors are present.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Electrical Safety</h3>
      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Grounding required.</strong> This tool must be grounded while in use to protect the operator from electric shock. It is equipped with a 3-conductor cord and 3-prong grounding plug. Never connect the green (or green/yellow) grounding wire to a live terminal. Use only 3-wire extension cords with 3-prong grounding plugs.
      </div>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Never change motor direction while the motor is running.</strong> Changing direction while running can damage the motor or flexible shaft and may cause injury. Always stop the motor completely before switching between forward and reverse.
      </div>

