      <h3>Shaft and Sheath Adjustment</h3>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-sr/p04_02.png" alt="Diagram showing shaft extending 3/4 inch beyond sheath" />
        <figcaption>Shaft must extend 3/4&Prime; (19 mm) beyond the sheath</figcaption>
      </div>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-sr/p04_03.png" alt="Motor connector set screw and shaft adjustment diagram" />
        <figcaption>Shaft and sheath assembly detail</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Remove the handpiece by pulling it off the shaft and sheath with a firm grip.</li>
        <li>Place the entire unit on a flat surface with shaft and sheath extended straight.</li>
        <li>Loosen the set screw on the motor connector.</li>
        <li>Adjust the exposed tip (handpiece end) of the flexible shaft so it extends 3/4&Prime; (19 mm) beyond the sheath. Move the sheath in or out of the motor connector.</li>
        <li>Retighten the set screw on the motor connector.</li>
        <li>Re-attach the handpiece.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        <strong>Important:</strong> The shaft and sheath should be checked and adjusted even if you received them pre-assembled and attached to the motor.
      </div>

      <h3>Attaching the Handpiece</h3>
      <div class="image-row">
        <div class="figure">
          <img src="/manuals/foredom-sr/p04_04.png" alt="Key tip end of shaft" />
          <figcaption>Key tip end of shaft</figcaption>
